quirements: 20 gauge IV</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Communication</key><value>Bowel prep for CT Colonography with normal kidney function (see brochure provided by CT).Kit Includes: 1 box Picosalax, 2x10 mg Bisacodyl rectal suppositories, Oral Barium Solution - 225 ml, Oral Telebrix - 30 ml.Two days prior: After supper clear fluids only.Day prior: Breakfast - 1 package of Picoslax in water, 4-5 more glasses of clear fluid in the next hour. 1 hour later 112ml Barium and clear fluids only, Snack - popsicle or decaffeinated soft drink, Lunch - Broth, 112ml Barium, Snack - popsicle or decaffeinated soft drink, Dinner- second package of Picosalax, drinking 4-5 glasses of clear fluids after, 8PM- 30 ml Telebrix with 8 oz clear fluid, insert 1 rectal suppository, after Midnight - no fluids except sip for medication.Two hours prior: Insert rectal suppository, sips of fluid for medications, empty bowel prior to the test.;Bowel prep for CT Colonography for impaired renal function and a GRF value less than 60 (see brochure provided by CT).Kit Includes: Colyte, 2x10 mg Biscodyl rectal suppositories, 2x25 mg Gravol tablets, Oral Barium Solution - 225 ml, Oral Telebrix - 30 ml.Two days prior: After supper clear fluids only.Day prior: Breakfast - 112ml Barium and clear fluids only, Snack - popsicle or decaffeinated soft drink, Lunch - Broth and 1 25mg Gravol, 112ml Barium, 1PM - Colyte, one glass every 15 min, finish up to 2 L, Snack - popsicle or decaffeinated soft drink, Dinner - 1 25mg Gravol, clear fluids only, 8PM - 30 ml Telebrix with 8 oz clear fluid, insert 1 rectal suppository, After midnight - no fluids except sip for medication.Two hours prior: Insert rectal suppository, Sips of fluid for medications, Empty bowel prior to the test.;Specific Site Variation (Edmonton - Outpatients only):Kit Includes: 2 x 10 mg of Buscopan (Buscopan may be substituted with 1 x 20 mg of Bentylol)2 hours prior: 2 x 10 mg Buscopan orallyInpatients will receive Buscopan  IV/IM.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Synonyms</key><value>CT Colon;CT Virtual Colonoscopy</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Resources </key><value>http://insite.albertahealthservices.ca/assets/policy/clp-di-prov-dis2-2-1-rad-protect-female-pts.pdf</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="CT Colonography"/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B48161A11EF4549FFAE82EE73B385AF5</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017E1FD7AC82EBDEE0202A6</digest></integrity_checks></template>